@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title The Same Injected Faults Can Still Produce Different Executions

actor Alice
box "Cluster" #E6F3FF
participant athens
participant byzantium
participant cyrene
end box

== Run 1 ==
Alice -> athens : set("title", "Microservices")
athens -> byzantium : replicate write
byzantium --> athens : ack arrives early
athens ->x cyrene : message lost
athens --> Alice : success

== Run 2 ==
Alice -> athens : set("title", "Microservices")
athens -> byzantium : replicate write
athens ->x cyrene : message lost
... ack delayed ...
byzantium --> athens : ack arrives later
athens -> athens : timeout / retry path differs

note over athens,cyrene #FFF2CC
Same injected fault and same write can still lead to a different execution trace
because internal timing changes when acknowledgements become visible.
end note

@enduml
